_**How does it work?**_
- **Fill in the** [**form**](https://forms.office.com/Pages/ResponsePage.aspx?id=erXza7Sfwkea2lEVZRj1L79C41kYRTJNqj_HxrI9Os5UQ0ZBNk5GTzlISDRQMTJJWU1COE5YNFowUS4u) with your information and the subjects for which you need tutoring;
- Learning Needs Help Desk will match you with the most suitable tutor;
- **Matching meeting**: you and the tutor will meet (online via teams) under the supervision of an expert to get to know each other and understand which study methods work best for you;
- You and your tutor can start meeting on your own, online or on campus. If you would like to use the Campus Life space, please send an email to [learningneeds.hd@unibocconi.it](mailto:learningneeds.hd@unibocconi.it) at least 2 days before the lesson.
**For further details:**

[learningneeds.hd@unibocconi.it](mailto:learningneeds.hd@unibocconi.it)

#### Information for student tutors

_**How to become a tutor**_

To apply, you must:
- [**check the list of required courses**](https://www.unibocconi.it/wps/wcm/connect/bocconi/sitopubblico_it/albero+di+navigazione/home/corsi+di+studio/studenti+iscritti/campus+life/counseling%2C+self-empowerment+e+wellbeing/self-empowerment/bacheca+corsi+per+tutor+peer+to+peer);
- **fill in the** [**registration form**](https://forms.office.com/Pages/ResponsePage.aspx?id=erXza7Sfwkea2lEVZRj1L79C41kYRTJNqj_HxrI9Os5UMFFUOVlZWFEwWDA1UTRXVkhRNjZKSkdKMC4u) indicating the subjects/courses indicated in the list you would feel most comfortable giving support in. If you want, you can also point out other subjects not on the list for which you would make yourself available for tutoring (in case of additional needs from SpLD students).
- **participate in a mandatory training meeting**
- Being able to dedicate **at least 1 hour a week** to this activity.
Tutors will be matched with SpLd students interested in the tutoring service and they will support them in preparing those classes and exams they need to be helped with.

All phases of the project will be coordinated by **Dr Milena Milani**, Educational Psychologist and member of the British Dyslexia Association.

This initiative is part of the activities that potentially qualify for the **Bocconi Social Impact Recognition project**. Find out more [on this page](https://www.unibocconi.it/wps/wcm/connect/bocconi/sitopubblico_en/navigation+tree/home/programs/current+students/campus+life/social+engagement/bocconi+social+impact+recognition_eng)!

_**Agenda**_
- **Mandatory training meeting:** tutors will meet via teams with Dr Milena Milani who will provide an overview of SpLD and strategies to support students. (Date to be defined);
- **Matching meeting**: the tutors and the students with SpLDs will meet with an expert. (Date to be defined);
- SpLD students will meet independently with their tutor;
- Some follow up meeting/s with an expert to monitor the tutoring activity and ensure that the match is working.

Foreign languages are classified as follows:
- **“Curricular” languages (UE languages):**
  - such languages are usually registered in the academic career as first/second language; cpu are included in the standard 180 /120 /300 cpu of the study plan (please find in the [Guide to the University](https://www.unibocconi.it/wps/wcm/connect/bocconi/sitopubblico_en/navigation+tree/info/current+students/guide+to+the+university) detailed information about how to choose curricular languages, minimum exit levels and teaching services);
  - moreover, they can be registered in the academic career as “extra activities” (4 cpu); cpu are recorded on top of standard 180/120/300 cpu of the study plan.
- **“Extra” languages:**
  - such languages can be registered in the academic career as “extra activities” only (4 cpu); therefore cpu are recorded on top of standard 180 /120 /300 cpu of the study plan.
English, Italian, French, Spanish and German are “curricular” languages.

Arabic, Chinese, Japanese, Russian are “extra” languages.

Portuguese is:
- “curricular” language up to a.y. 2018-19: it can be choosen as first /second language up to a.y. 2018-19;
- “extra” language as of a.y. 2019-20: as of 2019-20 students (any cohort) cannot choose it as first/second language any more.
International certifications (curricular and extra languages) can be registered in the academic curriculum provided that they are:
- officially recognized by Bocconi University (see the list below);
- submitted to the Administrative Office of the Language Center before the “expiry date” which is within 3 years after sitting the international certification exam (2 years for the international test TOEFL and – as of Sept 1st 2019 – for the IELTS test as well);
- submitted by the owner of the international certification (who is required to show his/her personalized Bocconi ID card);
- original certifications or statement of results (with stamp and signature of the certifying agency) only are allowed for submission.

## **The virtual learning environment**

Bocconi University uses the **Blackboard** e-learning platform to support the University's educational activities, accessible at the address [blackboard.unibocconi.it](https://blackboard.unibocconi.it/webapps/portal/execute/tabs/tabAction?tab_tab_group_id=_2_1) through university credentials.

Faculty members and students can access a **virtual teaching environment** which, thanks to the use of innovative teaching methods, allows them to create, manage and follow lessons and courses interactively with the help of discussion blogs, videoconferencing, tests, online assessments and more.

Furthermore, in each course present in the platform, additional tools and features are **integrated** and **available** for:

- scheduling, creating and recording **videoconferences**, webinars and individual meetings remotely ( **Blackboard Collaborate Ultra**);
- **preventing** plagiarism and encouraging the correct citation of resources in assignments ( **SafeAssign**);
- creating and sharing **videos** of any type, with the opportunity to track user views by user or create video quizzes ( **Kaltura**);
- to make use of the **Library**'s digital and physical resources ( [**Course Reserves**](https://lib.unibocconi.it/en/screens/textbooks/ "Course Reserves"));
- assigning the **textbooks** required for each course ( **EGEA Content Catalog**);
- using the learning platforms of the leading textbook providers ( **Pearson** and **McGraw-Hill**);
- carrying out programming assignments ( **Gradescope**);
- carrying out tests with advanced mathematical questions ( **WIRIS Quizzes**).

Other useful tools for teaching and research that are not yet integrated into the platform:

- [Microsoft Office 365](https://office.unibocconi.it/) (access allowed only to students with university credentials);
- [Qualtrics - Survey system for research and teaching](https://qualtrics.unibocconi.it/) (access with university credentials).

Technology and Information Services

[Overview](https://www.unibocconi.it/en/current-students/technology-and-information-services)


The IT infrastructure and University network systems offices have the duty of administrating the University IT system and managing the applications, hardware and software that make up the structure supporting the network. In particular, the offices manage all internal servers where all the applications used at the University are stored.

Activities:

- find the most advanced and secure solutions for the use of resources and information through both the cabled and wireless network infrastructures;
- administration of the email service used by the University and SDA Bocconi Students, Faculty and Staff;
- implementation of IT solutions set out in test projects in progress in the IT innovations area; included are the technology used for multi-videoconference systems and the podcasting service to support lessons;
- administration of the University portal and the e-learning portal; administration of the internal profiling system, based on LDAP Novell;
- administration of the Apple Podcast and video streaming system, as well as backup procedures;
- management of software for users connected to the network used by Students, Faculty and Staff;
- organizational management of Student computer labs, with constant updates of the standard and scientific application packages for all IT equipment;
- implementation and management of the network connectivity at each building on the University campus.

